12 vices to retain fingerprint cards obtained pursuant to this section.
13 (7) In addition to the rules required by ORS 181A.195, the Department of Human Services and
14 the Oregon Health Authority, in consultation with the Department of State Police, shall adopt rules:
15 (a) Specifying which qualified entities are subject to this section;
16 (b) Specifying which qualified entities may request criminal offender information;
17 (c) Specifying which qualified entities are responsible for deciding, subject to rules adopted by
18 the Oregon Department of Administrative Services under ORS 181A.215, whether a subject individ-
19 ual is not fit for a position, service, license, certification, registration or employment; and
20 (d) Specifying when a qualified entity, in lieu of conducting a completely new criminal records
21 check, may proceed to make a fitness determination under subsection (5) of this section using the
22 information maintained by the Department of Human Services and the Oregon Health Authority
23 pursuant to subsection (6) of this section.
24 (8) If a person refuses to consent to the criminal records check or refuses to be fingerprinted,
25 the qualified entity shall deny or terminate the employment of the person, or revoke or deny any
26 applicable position, authority to provide services, employment, license, certification or registration.
27 (9) If the qualified entity requires a criminal records check of employees or other persons, the
28 application forms of the qualified entity must contain a notice that employment is subject to fin-
29 gerprinting and a criminal records check.
30 SECTION 8. ORS 443.008 is amended to read:
31 443.008. (1) As used in this section:
32 (a) “Direct care services” means services provided to clients of the Department of Human Ser-
33 vices or the Oregon Health Authority by:
34 (A) An adult foster home, as defined in ORS 443.705;
35 (B) A home care worker, as defined in ORS 410.600;
36 (C) A residential facility, as defined in ORS 443.400; or
37 (D) A service provider as defined in ORS 427.101.
38 (b) “Fitness determination” means the evaluation of whether a subject individual or other indi-
39 vidual providing direct care services is fit to hold a position, provide direct care services or be
40 granted a license, certification, registration or permit to provide direct care services.
41 (c) “Qualified entity” has the meaning given that term in ORS 181A.190.
42 (d) “Subject individual” means a person who is:
43 (A) Employed by or who seeks to be employed by the authority or the department;
44 (B) A volunteer or who seeks to be a volunteer to provide care on behalf of the authority or the
45 department; or
[10]

HB 4115
1 (C) Providing care or who seeks to provide care on behalf of the authority or the department.
2 (2) The department and the authority shall prescribe by rule the criteria to be considered in
3 making fitness determination findings of abuse that are substantiated. The criteria must include the
4 types of substantiated abuse for which a subject individual may be found to be unfit and conditions,
5 if any, for the reinstatement of a subject individual who is found to be unfit.
6 (3) A subject individual who is found to be unfit is entitled to challenge the fitness determination
7 in a contested case hearing conducted in accordance with ORS chapter 183. The subject individual
8 may not challenge a finding of substantiated abuse or criminal conviction that was the basis for the
9 fitness determination but may contest the weight accorded the evidence, mitigating factors or other
10 aspects of the evaluation. The individual may be represented by an attorney or other person or, if
11 the individual is a member of a bargaining unit, by the certified or recognized exclusive represen-
12 tative for the bargaining unit.
13 (4) This section applies to fitness determinations for providers of direct care services conducted
14 under ORS 181A.195 (10) or 443.004 [(7)] (9).
15 SECTION 9. This 2026 Act takes effect on the 91st day after the date on which the 2026
16 regular session of the Eighty-third Legislative Assembly adjourns sine die.
